The speed up dlc is there for people who are impatient.   So amazing I had to buy the japanese version before it was in english. (It was not hard to figure out if you play alot of kariosoft games like I do.) The game brings me back to my ski resort tycoon days but it is more unique than that. I love the idea of using plans and items to unlock new things. I played it all the way through and I love the crazy visitors like a cow and alien. I love how they can get wacky with these games that seem serious. The game felt good the whole way through as it was cheering you on every step of the way. It just kept getting better. I was hoping for more stuff to unlock because I was totally addicted to placing new objects to make combos. Thank you kariosoft you rock!

Looks like Kairosoft of old has returned! Before we continue, I must admit to being worried seeing IAPs in a paid game, but was very relieved to find that the game just allows you the option of paying to get some end game items immediately. Everything is still earnable the old fashioned way!  Your standard Kairosoft experience is here, ie combos, research, items, upgrades et al. The new gimmick on display is that you also manage your snow field (lifts, decorations, lighting, etc) in addition to putting combos in your resort. Clearing the woods to expand your field is required in order to find materials needed to research and upgrade.  A solid Kairosoft experience, of the type we've missed for a while. Here's hoping they continue along this road to recovering our faith and fandom!
